Tests practical implementation of SageMaker for anomaly detection, focusing on real-time latency requirements, data residency constraints, and phased deployment strategies using canary releases.

## Key Concepts
- Anomaly detection models (Isolation Forest, autoencoders)
- Time-series feature engineering (rolling windows)
- Endpoint configuration and autoscaling (min/max instances, latency targets)
- Monitoring and drift detection (SageMaker Clarify, CloudWatch)
- Cost optimization and regional data compliance

