## Why This Is Asked
This question tests practical use of SageMaker multi-model endpoints, per-tenant routing, and controlled releases under data privacy constraints (PrivateLink). It blends model choice, infrastructure sizing, and a measurable validation plan suitable for entry-level engineers.

## Key Concepts
- SageMaker multi-model endpoints and Model Registry
- Tenant-aware routing with API Gateway + Lambda
- PrivateLink data isolation and VPC considerations
- Canary rollouts and rollback criteria

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudocode for tenant routing to a variant
function routeTenant(req){
  const tenant = req.headers['x-tenant'];
  const variant = registry.getVariant(tenant);
  return endpoint.invoke({Body: req.body, Variant: variant});
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you test tenant isolation in practice?
- How would you monitor per-tenant drift and trigger rollbacks?
